        "formula": "Given input X of shape (N, C_in, L_in) and weight W of shape (C_in, C_out, K), the transposed 1D convolution with stride S=1, padding P=0, dilation D=1, output_padding OP=0, groups G=1 produces output Y of shape (N, C_out, L_out) where L_out = (L_in - 1)*S - 2*P + D*(K-1) + OP + 1 = 65538. For n in [0, N), o in [0, C_out), l in [0, L_out): Y[n,o,l] = sum_{i=0}^{C_in-1} sum_{k=0}^{K-1} W[i,o,K-1-k] * X[n,i,l+k-(K-1)], treating out-of-range X indices as zero. In other words, define W'[o,i,k] = W[i,o,K-1-k] and X_pad by padding X with K-1 zeros on both ends; then Y is the standard 1D convolution of W' over X_pad with stride S=1 and padding 0.",
        "boundary_treatment": "Out-of-bound accesses to X (when l+k-(K-1) < 0 or >= L_in) result in zero contribution (implicit zero-padding). The input X is effectively padded with K-1=2 zeros on each side of the length dimension before the convolution. No further output clipping is performed.",
